picked up by the <em>New Yorker</em>. The columns in this book are collected
from his pieces for that magazine and address with reflection and investigation
the various difficulties of modern medicine.</dd>

<dt>George Saunders, <em><a href="http://books.theinfo.org/go/159448242X">In Persuasion Nation: Stories</a></em></dt>
<dd>I have to be honest with you. I&#8217;m not really one for science fiction. Indeed,
I&#8217;m not a big fan of fiction in general. But George Saunders is different:
I&#8217;ll read just about anything by him. Saunders&#8217; stories manage to combine 
