<dt>Thomas Geoghegan, <em><a href="http://books.theinfo.org/go/1565848861">Which Side Are You On?: Trying to Be for Labor When It&#8217;s Flat on Its Back</a></em></dt>
<dd>One would think a book on labor history would be dreadfully dull and, more to the 
point, depressing. And yet, in the first chapter of this book, I found something 
